WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.320
As R users, we know that sometimes code is the best way to handle things, and in this

00:00:08.320 --> 00:00:14.540
video walkthrough, we'll be focused on setting up our access to the rscloud package.

00:00:14.540 --> 00:00:20.000
To get started using the rscloud package, we first need to set up our client credentials,

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:23.040
and we do this from within RStudio Cloud.

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:28.600
After logging in to our RStudio Cloud account, we can click on our icon or photo in the top

00:00:28.600 --> 00:00:34.560
right to access the user panel, and then select Client Credentials.

00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:38.880
This will take us to a page with any existing credentials we might have.

00:00:38.880 --> 00:00:44.759
To create new credentials, click on Plus New Credentials in the top right.

00:00:44.759 --> 00:00:48.320
This will open a popup where you can name your credentials.

00:00:48.320 --> 00:00:53.480
After naming your credentials, click OK to see and copy your generated credentials.

00:00:53.480 --> 00:00:57.599
You will only be shown the credentials once, so do be sure to copy them and store them

00:00:57.599 --> 00:01:00.840
in a secure place before closing the popup window.

00:01:00.840 --> 00:01:05.239
Be careful not to share or commit your credentials to Git.

00:01:05.239 --> 00:01:10.720
The recommended method for setting your credentials is by editing your R Environ file, and we

00:01:10.720 --> 00:01:14.440
can do this using the usethis package.

00:01:14.440 --> 00:01:21.639
From within RStudio Cloud, we can go to a project, and by running usethis, edit renviron

00:01:21.639 --> 00:01:23.639
in the console.

00:01:23.680 --> 00:01:28.040
This should then open your R Environ file, where you can paste and save your client credentials

00:01:28.040 --> 00:01:30.879
before restarting R.

00:01:30.879 --> 00:01:35.120
After setting up your credentials in your R Environ file, you can install the development

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:40.800
version of the rscloud package by running the following commands in the console.

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:47.879
install .packages remote and remotes install github rstudio rscloud

00:01:47.879 --> 00:01:53.279
Once this is done, you have the rscloud package available and ready to use in RStudio Cloud.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:59.760
From here, we can do things like run rscloud underscore space underscore list, which will

00:01:59.760 --> 00:02:05.760
return a table with all of the spaces available within our RStudio Cloud account, and we can

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:12.199
use a space underscore id from this table to look at the number of users and projects.

00:02:12.199 --> 00:02:19.979
For example, when I run rscloud underscore space using the space id 81721, I can see

00:02:19.979 --> 00:02:27.580
that there are 327 users and 946 projects within this shared workspace.

00:02:27.580 --> 00:02:32.880
You can learn more about additional functionality of the rscloud package by visiting the package

00:02:32.880 --> 00:02:37.380
documentation at github.com rstudio rscloud.

00:02:49.979 --> 00:02:51.979
rstudio rscloud.com

